            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e207a1310">
            <label>7</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e214" publication-type="other">
EC Directive 77/336.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e221a1310">
            <label>8</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e228" publication-type="other">
Van Tiem v. Staatssecretaris van Financien (ECJ Case C-186/89) 1993 STC 91.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e235a1310">
            <label>9</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e242" publication-type="other">
In the European Court cases the Advocate-General acts independently to summarise the arguments submitted to
the court and gives his opinion as to how the case should be decided. The Advocate-General's opinion may be cited
as authority for an argument. The often lengthy analysis he gives is to be contrasted with the terse formal style of
the Court's decision.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e258a1310">
            <label>10</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e265" publication-type="other">
Article 2 EC Directive 67/227.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e273a1310">
            <label>11</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e280" publication-type="other">
An ordinary investor does not pass its costs onto the company in which it participates.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e287a1310">
            <label>12</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e294" publication-type="other">
See, for example, a recent VAT tribunal decision where the costs of acquiring shares of a company and transferring
the business of that company to a purchases was deductible in full, UBAF Bank Limited v. The Commissioners of
Customs &amp; Excise, London VAT Tribunal LON/91/2623Y.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e307a1310">
            <label>13</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e314" publication-type="other">
On the basis of the UBAF decision, given in February 1993, the company buying shares could recover the VAT
if it immediately transfers the subsidiary company's business to itself.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e324a1310">
            <label>14</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e331" publication-type="other">
Leesportefeuille 'Intiem' v. Staatssecretaris van Justifie 2 CMLR 1989 856.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d57e338a1310">
            <label>15</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d57e345" publication-type="other">
On the broad view that a managing holding company is assimilated into its subsidiaries, the correct approach
would be to treat the holding company as making supplies in each Member State in which its subsidiaries make
supplies, and register it accordingly.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
